cs.NE, cs.BIO, cs.ET, cs.MS, cs.RO 

The paper discusses the use of biological substrates for generating novel computing devices, which falls under the category of computational neuroscience (cs.NE) and bioinformatics (cs.BIO). The study involves the manipulation of living organisms, which could also be classified under the categories of emerging technologies (cs.ET) and modeling and simulation (cs.MS). Finally, the study involves the use of nanoparticles for biohybridisation, which could also be classified under the category of robotics (cs.RO) as it involves the creation of self-growing hybrid circuitry.
